// Man page for scanaddress
manScanaddress="SCANADDRESS(1)                    X Shell Manual                SCANADDRESS(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    scanaddress - Scan a memory zone address in a library for vulnerabilities

<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>scanaddress</b> [-av] LIB_PATH ZONE [ZONE...]
    command | <b>scanaddress</b> [-v] LIB_PATH
    <b>scanaddress</b> -a [-v] LIB_PATH

<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Runs scan_address on one or more memory zone addresses in a .so library.
    Zone addresses can be passed as arguments or piped from stdin (e.g. from
    scanlib). Requires metaxploit.

<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>-a</b>    Auto mode. Calls scan internally to find all zones and scans each
          one. No need to pipe from scanlib.
    <b>-v</b>    Verbose. Prints each zone address before scanning it.

<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <b>scanaddress -a /lib/crypto.so</b>
    Scan all zones automatically

    <b>scanlib /lib/libhttp.so | scanaddress /lib/libhttp.so</b>
    Scan all zones found by scanlib

    <b>scanlib /lib/libhttp.so | head -n 1 | scanaddress /lib/libhttp.so</b>
    Scan only the first zone found by scanlib

    <b>scanaddress -av /lib/libhttp.so | grep exploit</b>
    Auto-scan verbosely and filter for exploits

<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>scanlib</b>, <b>0day</b>, <b>lms</b>"
